wiki.summary: In a video discussing the creation of “The Making of Head on Fire”, Griff and Sigrid said that this song is about that moment when you really can’t get someone out of your head. Griff also noted that this was her first time working with another artist rather than just a producer. “Griff and I met sharing a pizza at the Rueben Selby show at Fashion Week in London…We went to the studio a while later and just had a day of talking about life, before writing ‘Head On Fire’.“ Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: In a video discussing the creation of “The Making of Head on Fire”, Griff and Sigrid said that this song is about that moment when you really can’t get someone out of your head. Griff also noted that this was her first time working with another artist rather than just a producer. “Griff and I met sharing a pizza at the Rueben Selby show at Fashion Week in London…We went to the studio a while later and just had a day of talking about life, before writing ‘Head On Fire’.“ — Sigrid via NME “I’ve looked up to Sigrid so much, especially as a young girl who broke through making powerful, credible pop music. So I was excited to hear she wanted to write. We hung out and made ‘Head On Fire’, this really fun, feel-good song, and I’m excited for the world to finally hear us on a track together.“ — Griff via NME “It’s about that feeling when you meet someone who just flips everything upside down and you can’t focus on anything else but that person. [Griff’s] just lovely, and it’s been so much fun working with her.“ — Sigrid via NME Read more on Last.fm.
